Subject: distance between plants
Value: The distance of a whole plant

Subject: distance between rows
Value: Average distance between plants in a same row.@en

Subject: irrigation process
Value: A planned process in which water is artificially supplied to plant or soil to sustain plants. @en

Subject: row
Value: two or more crop plants planted in a line.@en

Subject: moisture concentration measurement protocol
Value: <1.Weight a sample of the material. 2.Dry this sample. 3.Weight the dry sample. Moisture concentration = ((Ww-Wd)/Ww) x 100 in which : WW = wet weight of the sample, and Wd = weight of the sample after drying.@en>

Subject: sunken seedbed
Value: a seedbed that is below the surrounding soil level. Sunken beds conserve water much more effectively than raised bed

Subject: biochar
Value: charcoal used as a soil amendment.

Subject: bird guano
Value: an animal manure composoed of the excrement of seabirds and bats.

Subject: tillage
Value: group together tillage and no-till processes
